-- Unicaja Needs to Raise 888 Million Euros in Further Provisions
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-05-13T10:57:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/unicaja-needs-to-raise-888-million-euros-in-further-provisions.html
Unicaja Banco, which is merging with
rival Banco Ceiss, said it needs 888 million euros ($1.2
billion) to comply with increased provisions demanded by the
Spanish government.  Banks will have to raise capital to provide for potential
losses on 123 billion euros of real estate-linked loans and the
government will provide funds for those needing support, Economy
Minister Luis de Guindos said May 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
